10005,"How to pull an element from an array of arrays in Mongo

I am struggling to find the format for a query to remove an element (with an _id) from an array of arrays in Mongo via Mongoose. I have read the Mongo documentation on pull and searched around, but cannot get the query format correct.
I know: the _id of the document in MySchema, the _id of the array element in outerArray, and the _id of the the array element in innerArray.
Could someone please point out what I am doing wrong? Thank you!

,@Reem: Sounds like your `script` tag is probably in the wrong place. Script code runs as soon as the `script` tag is encountered, so if the `script` tag is *above* the HTML for the elements, they won't exist when you run `getElementById` and it'll return `null`. Unless you have a reason to do something else, put your `script` tags at the end of the HTML, just before the closing `` tag. More: [**](https://developer.yahoo.com/performance/rules.html#js_bottom)","Embed Field: How to pull an element from an array of arrays in Mongo
